#Here, the main deck will be displayed. Clicking on the deck draws a card into your hand. Clicking on a card activates that card.

{!<div class="scrollable-box">!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 1: It is a bright time for German democracy. After a period of struggle, inflation is finally under control, and the economy is expanding steadily. In foreign policy, we have reached agreements with the Western powers and the <span style="color: #750e0e;">Soviet Union</span> that might make genuine peace a reality. <br><br> Now, the task of <span style="color: #c00000;">Social Democracy</span> is to prepare for the next election. The <span style="color: #000000;">bourgeois</span>-<span style="color: #3E88B3;">right</span> government of Wilhelm Marx is unpopular, and we stand to gain. Perhaps the next government will have a <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> majority. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 2 : The current <span style="color: #000000;">bourgeois</span>-<span style="color: #3E88B3;">right</span> government has fallen. The next elections are slated for May of this year. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 3 : Special interest parties such as the <span style="color: #b8996f;">Reich Party of the Middle Class</span>—commonly referred to as the <span style="color: #b8996f;">Economic Party</span>(<span style="color: #b8996f;">**WP**</span>)—and the <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">Christian-National Peasants' and Farmers' Party</span>(<span style="color: #7FCEB1;">**CNBLP**</span>) are expected to gain a decent foothold in the Reichstag, due to the belief that the established political parties are neglecting their interests. This negatively impacts the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>, having been part of the last government. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 4 : The right-wing industrial forces in the <span style="color: #C0A054;">People's Party</span>(<span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>) has been gaining considerable influence within the party due to party leader and Foreign Minister Gustav Stresemann's neglect of internal party affairs. The prospect of a Grand Coalition with the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> is becoming increasingly difficult, especially with Stresemann's declining health. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 4 : Our neighbor <span style="color: #002654;">France</span> has held its legislative elections, resulting in a defeat for the <span style="color: #FFC0C0;">Left Cartel</span>, and the continuation of right-wing cabinets. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 5 : The voting age for women in <span style="color: #C8102E;">Great Britain</span> has been lowered from 30 to 21, another day another banger. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 6 : A round of internal in-fighting has arisen within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> following their poor results in the last election. A controversial article from Walther Lambach, a prominent member of the "Christian Socialist" wing of the party, blames the results on the talk of restoring of the monarchy as unrealistic and calls for the party to open up to conservative <span style="color: #000000;">rep</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">ubl</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">icans</span>. [? if in_right_coalition or in_right_coalition_prussia : Furthermore, their participation in government in the system they're fundamentally opposed has created a rift with the radical right elements within their party. ?] [? if pro_republic >= 65 or ((pro_republic >= 57 and in_right_coalition and in_right_coalition_prussia) or (pro_republic >= 59 and in_right_coalition) or (pro_republic >= 62 and in_right_coalition_prussia)): His controversial take has surprisingly found some support within the party. ?]Alfred Hugenberg and his allies on the right of the party are seeking to capitalize on monarchist anger against Lambach to seize control in the party congress this October. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 6 : The poor showing for the liberal parties has convinced their leadership that Germany no longer has the luxury of two liberal parties. However, the prospect of a merger is held back by the left <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> and the right <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>, who are strongly against compromising their own interests. Despite this, a parliamentary group between the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> and <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> is seeming likely. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 7 : Kuno von Westarp, the moderate leader of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>, has resigned as party leader following conflict with Hugenberg and his allies. Westarp, although opposed to Lambach's views, refrained from expelling him from the party to prevent a possible succession from the party's left wing, to the outrage of many monarchists. [? if pro_republic < 65 and not ((pro_republic >= 57 and in_right_coalition and in_right_coalition_prussia) and not (pro_republic >= 59 and in_right_coalition) and not (pro_republic >= 62 and in_right_coalition_prussia)): This has prompted Westarp to resign as chairman, and Lambach to be expelled from the party due to unrelenting attacks from Hugenberg's allies. ?][? if pro_republic >= 65 or ((pro_republic >= 57 and in_right_coalition and in_right_coalition_prussia) or (pro_republic >= 59 and in_right_coalition) or (pro_republic >= 62 and in_right_coalition_prussia)): This has prompted Westarp to resign as chairman due to unrelenting attacks from Hugenberg's allies, but Lambach is saved from expulsion by the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>'s left wing. ?] Meanwhile, Hugenberg and his allies in the Pan-German League have been garnering considerable support within their local party organizations. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 7 and (liberal_vote >= 13 and peoples_party_support < 2) or (in_right_coalition or in_weimar_coalition) and next_election_time - time >= 3: The efforts of Stresemann and the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> under Koch-Weser to strengthen ties between their two parties have been a failure due to the strong opposition voiced by the extreme wings of both parties. Stresemann is growing disillusioned with his own party, viewing it as a vehicle for industrial interests rather than liberal values. The leftists in the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> argue that the merger would have to take into account the interests of the working class, a policy vehemently opposed by the industrial interests. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and flavour_5_trigger == 1 and flavour_5_trigger_time == time: The impact of the last election to encourage cooperation between the two liberal parties have culminated in the creation of a parliamentary faction featuring the two parties. This is begrudgingly accepted by the extremes of both parties to increase their parliamentary influence with the declining liberal vote. <br><br> A new Liberal Association has been gaining traction with funding from both parties, and are expected to open up state and local chapters and to draft a policy program. This seems to be the prelude to the founding of a new liberal party, but it's not certain if both parties will consent to this. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and n_elections == 1 and next_election_time - time = 2: Our calls for new elections just after the last one have pushed the liberal parties closer together, in order to not face any further decline. A new Liberal Association has emerged coordinating the efforts of the two parties and seems to be the prelude to the founding of a new liberal party, but it's not certain if both parties would fully agree. <br><br> The idea of a liberal parliamentary faction has gained considerable traction with both parties and they are likely to negotiate as a single bloc after the election. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_timer == 4: The quest towards liberal unity has advanced, with the Liberal Association's influence growing within local chapters of the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> and <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> chapters on the local level. In the liberal stronghold of Baden-Württemberg, a merger between the two parties is already underway, even without formal approval from their national leadership. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 8 : Wilhelm Marx, leader of the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>, former chancellor, and presidential candidate, has resigned following his party's poor performance in the last election. A new leader is scheduled to be elected this December. <br><br> The <span style="color: #750e0e;">Soviet Union</span> has unveiled their first "Five-Year Plan" to rapidly industrialize their country. <br><br> We have won second place in the Summer Olympics in Amsterdam! ?] {!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 8 and pro_republic_7 < 65 and not (pro_republic_7 >= 57 and in_right_coalition and in_right_coalition_prussia) and not ((pro_republic_7 >= 59 and in_right_coalition) and not (pro_republic_7 >= 62 and in_right_coalition_prussia)): Lambach has been reinstated to the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> and their Reichstag delegation following pressure from the Christian labor movement and white-collar organizations. [? if in_right_coalition or in_right_coalition_prussia = 1: <br><br> Hugenberg's attempts to increase his influence within the party are complicated by the reality that if he were to bring down the current [? if in_right_coalition_prussia and in_right_coalition: Prussian and federal ?][? if in_right_coalition_prussia and not in_right_coalition: Prussian ?][? if in_right_coalition and not in_right_coalition_prussia: federal ?]coalition when elected, the only viable alternative for a parliamentary majority would be a government led by us. ?] ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_timer == 3: Stresemann and other high-ranking party officials, including the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>'s Koch-Weser, have been holding discreet meetings over the past few weeks to discuss a potential merger between their two parties. Meanwhile, numerous liberal youth organizations have been created with the goal of fostering cooperation between <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> and <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> for a united middle party. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 9 : After the poor performance of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> in the recent election, Adolf Hitler's ban on public speaking has been lifted. ?] {!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 9 and spd_in_government = 0 : The bourgeois government has approved construction of a new battlecruiser, as part of Germany's rearmament. We have gained some support as an opposition party advocating food for children instead of battleships. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 9 : Adam Stegerwald, chairman of the Catholic trade unions,[? if prussia_leader == "Stegerwald": and Minister-President of Prussia,?] is the frontrunner to succeed Wilhelm Marx. He advocates for a broad interconfessional “people’s bloc” over special interest groups. He is skeptical of cooperation with us.?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 9 : The President of Albania has declared the country to be a constitutional monarchy, crowning himself as King Zog I. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 9 : The <span style="color: #D70926;">Swedish Social Democrats</span> has suffered a defeat in their recent general election. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 9 : Westarp's refusal to run for re-election has left the moderate anti-Hugenberg forces within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> without a candidate. Hugenberg has shown ambivalence in the party chairmanship himself, and has shown interest in a triumvirate of sorts. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_timer == 2: Those on the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>'s left wing, who remain firmly opposed to a merger of the two parties, are being forced out of the party or sidelined to clear the path for unification. However, the right wing of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> holds significant sway over the party and the negotiations, prompting Stresemann to call for an emergency party congress to resolve the issue. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 10 and in_grand_coalition and (foreign_minister_party = "DVP" or foreign_minister_party = "LVP") and lvp_timer_trigger == 0: Stresemann is planning a large internal reform of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> spearheaded by Otto Thiel, a trade unionist. He strikes a strong parallel with Lambach in working to expand the party to attract all sectors of society. However, Stresemann's health has been declining and his foreign policy work takes precedent over potentially causing the right of his party to collapse the coalition. In the meantime, they will continue getting stronger. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 10 and not in_grand_coalition or not (foreign_minister_party = "DVP" or foreign_minister_party = "LVP") and lvp_timer_trigger == 0: Stresemann is planning a large internal reform of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> spearheaded by Otto Thiel, a trade unionist. He strikes a strong parallel with Lambach in working to expand the party to attract all sectors of society. Although Stresemann's health has been declining, he has finally shown focus to his party's internal affairs. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 10 : Hugo Eckener has successfully completed the first intercontinental flight of a zeppelin! The *Graf Zeppelin* departed from Germany and landed in New Jersey, marking the longest non-stop flight to date, lasting over 111 hours in the air. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 11 and not prussia_leader == "Stegerwald": Despite Stegerwald's strong position in the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>'s leadership race, he faces significant resistance from the party's middle class because of his ties to labor and his opposition to a proposed raise for civil servants. New candidates have emerged for the party congress in December. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 11 and prussia_leader == "Stegerwald": Stegerwald's position in the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>'s leadership race has been declining, due to significant resistance from the party's middle class because of his ties to labor and his opposition to a proposed raise for civil servants. New candidates have emerged for the party congress in December, creating a three-way contest. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 11 and not (in_grand_coalition == 0 or ((in_grand_coalition == 1 and in_grand_coalition_prussia == 1 and coalition_dissent < 1 and (foreign_minister_party = "DVP" or foreign_minister_party = "LVP")) or (in_grand_coalition == 1 and in_grand_coalition_prussia == 1 or coalition_dissent < 2 and (foreign_minister_party != "DVP" and foreign_minister_party != "LVP")))) and not lvp_formed and lvp_timer_trigger == 0: Stresemann has put off his plan to confront the right-wing of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> in order to not risk collapsing our government, following disputes involving the Prussian government and the <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span> Party. While this is good news for stability, the right wing of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> are going to give us more problems down the line.?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 11 and (in_grand_coalition == 0 or ((in_grand_coalition == 1 and in_grand_coalition_prussia == 1 and coalition_dissent < 1 and (foreign_minister_party = "DVP" or foreign_minister_party = "LVP")) or (in_grand_coalition == 1 and in_grand_coalition_prussia == 1 or coalition_dissent < 2 and (foreign_minister_party != "DVP" and foreign_minister_party != "LVP")))) and not lvp_formed and lvp_timer_trigger == 0: Stresemann and his allies in the left <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> have called a party congress to discuss internal reforms that would grant the party's middle class and worker elements a greater voice. Needless to say, the industrialists on the right vehemently oppose this plan, and will raise hell next party congress. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 11 : Herbert Hoover of the <span style="color: #E81B23;">Republican Party</span> has secured a landslide victory over <span style="color: #00AEF3;">Democrat</span> Al Smith in the <span style="color: #B31942;">United</span> <span style="color: #0A3161;">States</span> presidential election. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 11 : A cartoon by the name of *Steamboat Willie* has been released, the first of its kind to feature sound. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 12 and (in_center_right_coalition or in_right_coalition) and not lvp_formed and lvp_timer_trigger == 0: The entrance of the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> into the governing coalition has increased cooperation between to the two liberal parties, that have undergone a rightwards shift as of late. They've formed a common parliamentary faction with the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> in the Reichstag and party leaders are in talks about further efforts in cooperation. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1928 and month = 12 : The Chinese Nationalists of the <span style="color: #000099;">**KMT**</span> have reunited China, ending the warlord period. Japan remains as an imperialist force in the region however. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 1: Leon Trotsky has been exiled from the <span style="color: #750e0e;">Soviet Union</span> after losing his power struggle with <span style="color: #8B0000;">Stalin</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 1 and z_leader == "Stegerwald": The election of Stegerwald as chairman of the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> has triggered significant fallout, with mass defections among the party's middle-class and Catholic voters. The once stagnant party is transforming into a dynamic force, no longer held together by the cohesiveness of shared faith. Stegerwald is pushing ahead with his vision of an interconfessional party, and is [? if dnvp_ideology == "Moderate":establishing friendly relations with Protestant labor leaders within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>?][? if dnvp_ideology == "Radical":opening up branches in non-Catholic states?], but the process will be a long and arduous one. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 1: King Alexander I of Yugoslavia has established a <span style="color: #808080;">royal dictatorship</span> under the pretext of domestic political turmoil. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 1: The book *All Quiet on the Western Front* has been released with controversy. The novel describes the experiences of German soldiers in the Great War, and how they gradually became disillusioned with the ideas of patriotism and nationalism. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 3 and lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>'s former labor leaders and leftists, and even some <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> leftists such as Otto Thiel, have established the "Social Republican Circle." This faction aims to shift the party's platform from its current middle-class focus to one that also advocates for the interests of workers. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 3 and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> is continuing to bleed members of its left and labor wing to the <span style="color: #c00000;">socialists</span>, as an atmosphere of pessimism and disillusionment with the Weimar system begins setting in across the bourgeois parties. Once one of the strongest defenders of Weimar democracy, is now steadily fading into irrelevance and nationalism. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 4: The Danish <span style="color: #C82518;">Social Democrats</span> have emerged victorious in the recent *Folketing* election, forming a coalition with the <span style="color: #733280;">Social Liberals</span>. Thorvald Stauning has returned as Prime Minister, who will continue advancing an extensive welfare state, perhaps we can take inspiration? ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 5 and reichswehr_minister_party != "SPD": The Ministry of Defense has created a new position, the office for ministerial affairs, responsible for coordinating and implementing the Reichswehr’s strategy for dealing with the cabinet, the Reichstag, the various political parties, and, perhaps most importantly, the office of the Reich President. Recently promoted General Kurt von Schleicher, is appointed to this position by Wilhelm Groener. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 5 and in_right_coalition = 0 or in_center_right_coalition = 0 : The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> and a vast array of right-wing organizations have been preparing to launch a referendum[? if dnvp_ideology == "Radical":&nbsp;with Hugenberg's blessing?] to revise the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> constitution by allowing the president to appoint a chancellor without Reichstag consent and to lift immunity from Reichstag deputies charged with treason. Although the scope of the referendum is limited, it is intended to create a rallying point for the right[? if dnf_formed = 1:&nbsp;despite Hugenberg's non-participation?]. [? if dnf_formed = 1: Hugenberg and the <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span> are instead planning to initiate a referendum about foreign policy, although it is unlikely that it would reach the signature threshold. ?] ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 5 and not lvp_formed: Many youth groups are formed around the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> to rejuvenate the party against the industrial interests, and to advocate for a merger of bourgeois parties to rival the <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>. Stresemann has also been engaging in secret talks with the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>'s Koch-Weser over the last few months. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 5 and lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span> has found success in rallying middle-class youth under its banner, with an amalgam of youth groups merging into their "Young Liberals." This youth wing is noticeably more left-leaning than the broader party and will push for policies that will steer the <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span> toward a more progressive outlook. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 5 : The United Kingdom general election has returned a massive win for <span style="color: #f0456a;">Labour</span>, with them gaining over 100 seats. Despite this, they have fallen short of a majority and will govern in a minority government with the <span style="color: #FFD700;">Liberals</span> as kingmaker. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 5 : The <span style="color: #D70926;">Belgian Labour Party</span> has won the most votes in their recent general election, but the incumbent <span style="color: #FFD700;">Catholic</span>-<span style="color: #3C40D2;">Liberal</span> coalition continues. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 6 : After months of deliberation in Paris by [+ foreign_minister +], the Allied powers have crafted a set of proposals known as the Young Plan, which is to reduce our reparation payments and grant us more fiscal autonomy. The <span style="color: #002654;">French</span> have also agreed on an early withdrawal from the Rhineland in June 1930. [? if in_right_coalition = 1 or in_center_right_coalition = 1: The negotiations around the Young Plan has created a great deal of dissent with the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>, who oppose the plan and claim reparations are a form of national slavery. The coalition is unlikely to last much longer. ?][? if in_right_coalition = 0 and in_center_right_coalition = 0: While this seems to be a positive development for the country, the Right is campaigning hard against this plan, as are the <span style="color: #700000;">**Communists**</span> for whatever reason. ?] ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 6: Vatican City has been established through an agreement between Benito Mussolini and the Holy See, making it the world's newest country. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 6 and dnvp_ideology = "Radical" : Opposition to the referendum by the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> has caused Hugenberg to cancel his plans for the referendum for the revision of the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> constitution, to the frustration of many [? if dnvp_leader == "Hugenberg": <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> party members.?][? if dnvp_leader == "Triumvirate": many party members including Westarp.?] A campaign for a referendum against the Young Plan has begun, abandoning the progress the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has made with courting the [? if not lvp_formed: <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>?][? if lvp_formed: <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span>?] and <span style="color: #A2D8E0;">**BVP**</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 7 and dnvp_ideology = "Radical" : The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> has been given an important role in planning the referendum against the Young Plan, serving as a counter to the historical treatment of Hitler's <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> by the right. Hugenberg has been especially friendly in giving concessions to keep the seemingly tiny party in the "National Front". The lack of significant industrial support for this initiative has been forcing Hugenberg to use a substantial amount of his personal funds. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 7 and dnf_formed = 1 and not was_in_center_right_coalition : The <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span> is organizing a referendum against the Young Plan closely with the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>. The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> is in an internal battle whether to work with the <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span> on the referendum for a united right, or launch their own planned referendum on the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> constitution. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 7 and dnf_formed = 1 and was_in_center_right_coalition : The <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span> is organizing a referendum against the Young Plan closely with the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>. The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> is in an internal battle whether to work with the <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span> on the referendum for a united right, or to preserve relations with the bourgeois parties. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 8 and dnf_formed = 1 and was_in_center_right_coalition and pro_republic < 70: The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> has been given an important role in planning the referendum against the Young Plan, serving as a counter to the historical treatment of Hitler's <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> by the right. This includes the inclusion of a paragraph calling for the imprisonment of those responsible for signing, including President Hindenburg. This has led to the removal the paragraph to persuade the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>'s to support their initiative as without their backing, there would be nothing more than a humiliating defeat. Internal dissent within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has increased with the decision to cooperate with Hugenberg and Hitler. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 8 and dnf_formed = 1 and was_in_center_right_coalition and pro_republic >= 70 : The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> has been given an important role in planning the referendum against the Young Plan, serving as a counter to the historical treatment of Hitler's <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> by the right. This includes the inclusion of a paragraph calling for the imprisonment of those responsible for signing, including President Hindenburg. Even with the removal of the paragraph, the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> are still uncommitted to support the referendum together with the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">far</span>-<span style="color: #003755;">right</span>. Internal dissent within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has increased with the decision to not cooperate with the right on opposing "national slavery". ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 8 and dnf_formed = 1 and pro_republic >= 70 and not was_in_center_right_coalition : The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> has been given an important role in planning the referendum against the Young Plan, serving as a counter to the historical treatment of Hitler's <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> by the right. This includes the inclusion of a paragraph calling for the imprisonment of those responsible for signing, including President Hindenburg. Even with the removal of the paragraph, the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> is still going through with their own referendum. Internal dissent within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has increased with the decision to not cooperate with the right on opposing "national slavery". ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 8 and ddp_cohesion >= 12 and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> held its party congress, with little of note occurring beyond respected economist Gustav Stolper presenting his 'Stolper Program', which redefined the party's social and economic focus toward supporting the struggling middle classes over the industrial working class. Despite opposition from the party's left wing and labor groups, it has become their official economic program, sparking renewed enthusiasm among its grassroots and the German middle. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 8 and ddp_cohesion < 12 and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> held its party congress, with little of note occurring beyond respected economist Gustav Stolper presenting his 'Stolper Program', which redefined the party's social and economic focus toward supporting the struggling middle classes over the industrial working class. However, opposition from the party's left led to the quiet shelving of the plan, despite significant enthusiasm from the grassroots. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_1_timer == 4: Stresemann's secret negotiations with the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> have borne fruit, with the two parties converging on policy. The recently adopted Stolper Program and the transformation of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> into a genuine people's party, while keeping their industrial wing in check, have greatly eased the path toward greater cooperation between the two liberal parties. Larger scale negotiations will continue over the next few months. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 8 : Hugo Eckener has successfully completed the first circumnavigation of the globe in a zeppelin! The journey covered 33,234 kilometers in approximately 21 days, beginning and ending at the same launch site. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 8 and dnf_formed = 1 and pro_republic < 70 and not was_in_center_right_coalition: The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> has been given an important role in planning the referendum against the Young Plan, serving as a counter to the historical treatment of Hitler's <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> by the right. This includes the inclusion of a paragraph calling for the imprisonment of those responsible for signing, including President Hindenburg. This has led to the removal of the paragraph to persuade the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> to support their initiative as without their backing, there would be nothing more than a humiliating defeat. Internal dissent within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has increased with the decision to abandon previous plans. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 9 and dnf_formed = 1 and pro_republic_8 >= 70 and not was_in_center_right_coalition and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has gained the support of the bourgeois parties, the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #A2D8E0;">**BVP**</span>, in favor of their referendum to reform the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> constitution. [? if dvp_relation >= 40 and dvp_ideology_9 != "Right" : However, our friendly relations with them have stopped them from siding against us. ?] The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">far</span>-<span style="color: #003755;">right</span> parties are committed to their own referendum and will not be involved. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 9 and dnf_formed = 1 and pro_republic_8 >= 70 and not was_in_center_right_coalition and lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has failed to gain the support of the bourgeois parties, the right <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span> and <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>, in favor of the referendum to reform the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> constitution. Only the <span style="color: #A2D8E0;">**BVP**</span> has agreed to back the referendum. The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">far</span>-<span style="color: #003755;">right</span> parties are committed to their own referendum and will not be involved. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 9 and dnvp_leader = "Hugenberg": Within the last paragraph of the "Freedom Act", the subject of the referendum, lies a highly controversial "imprisonment" paragraph demanding that those responsible for signing the Young Plan should be charged for high treason and imprisoned, even President Hindenburg. This has caused great dissent within the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> and <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**Stahlhelm**</span>, but Hugenberg, inflexible as always, remains adamant about keeping the paragraph, as the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> made their support conditional on its retention. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 9 and dnvp_leader = "Triumvirate": Within the last paragraph of the "Freedom Act", the subject of the referendum, lies a highly controversial "imprisonment" paragraph demanding that those responsible for signing the Young Plan should be charged for high treason and imprisoned, even President Hindenburg. Hugenberg, inflexible as always, remains adamant about keeping the paragraph, as the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> made their support conditional on its retention. The paragraph has obviously sparked great criticism against Hugenberg and Westarp has resigned from the ruling triumvirate in protest. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 9 and spd_in_government and not lvp_formed: The right wing of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> have voiced disappointment with our government and urge us to enact a large fiscal reform to comply with the terms of the Young Plan. This includes cutting the unemployment insurance program, which is on the verge of bankruptcy as unemployment continues to rise. The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> insists on cutting benefits rather than increasing employer contributions, Stresemann is increasingly finding it harder to create compromise within his party. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_1_timer == 3: Despite this setback, the reform of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>'s party structure has made the demands of their industrialists far less threatening. [? if not stresemann_dead: Stresemann?][? if stresemann_dead: Curtius?] and other high-ranking party officials, including the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>'s Koch-Weser, have agreed to remove the most radical members of their respective parties to facilitate unification. Meanwhile, the previously moribund Liberal Association, in collaboration with various youth groups, has begun drafting a policy platform and forming local chapters. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 9: The Dow Jones Industrial Average has peaked at $381.17, the Golden Twenties continue! ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 10: The initiative against the Young Plan has finished collecting its signatures for it to become a referendum, with [+ young_plan_signatures +]% of eligible voters signing[? if young_plan_signatures >= 10 : [? if young_plan_signatures < 11 : &nbsp;barely?] exceeding the 10% minimum requirement.?][? if young_plan_signatures < 10 : [? if young_plan_signatures > 9 :&nbsp;barely?] falling short of the 10% minimum requirement. This will certainly spark some debates within the right-wing parties. ?] ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 10 and pro_republic_8 >= 70 and not was_in_center_right_coalition and dnf_formed = 1: The initiative for the revision of the constitution has finished collecting its signatures for it to become a referendum, with [+ weimar_ref_signatures +]% of eligible voters signing. The vote for the referendum will occur at the end of this year, with 50% of eligible voters requiring to vote in favor. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 10 and not lvp_formed: A small nationalist paramilitary, the Young German Order has formed a new political organization, the *People’s National Reich Association* (<span style="color: #D3D3A9;">**VNR**</span>), with the goal of becoming the crystallization point which a "great party of national regeneration" could form. Disillusioned <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> politicians such as Koch-Weser and Ernst Lemmer have shown interest in collaborating with this new party, to unite the German middle in a new "state party". This, however, complicates ongoing and any future discussions of a merger between the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_1_timer == 2: Stresemann's untimely death has complicated talks for a <span style="color: #FFCC00;">united liberal party</span>. His allies that are in the left <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> such as Otto Thiel and Julius Curtius are able to continue the negotiations, but there is a chance the unification may ultimately be blocked by the right-wing forces if they grow too powerful as a result of Stresemann's absence. Despite this, in the liberal stronghold of Baden-Württemberg, a merger between the two parties is already underway, even without formal approval from their national leadership. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 10: <span style="color: #f0456a;">Labor</span> has come into power in Australia. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 10 : The <span style="color: #D70926;">Czechoslovak Social Democrats</span> has won the most votes in their recent general election, with the more reformist <span style="color: #FAC469;">Czechoslovak (National) Socialist Party</span> not too far behind. The <span style="color: #A00500;">Communists</span> and other right-wing parties have suffered setbacks. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_1_timer == 1: The opposition to a <span style="color: #FFCC00;">united liberal party</span> extends beyond the right wing of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>. Many politicians of all factions within the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>, including Koch-Weser himself, have expressed interest in an alternative merger with the <span style="color: #D3D3A9;">**VNR**</span>. [? if lvp_trigger_2_time == time + 1: However, Koch-Weser and the business wing of the party has discredited the skeptics with the party, and will proceed with unification. ?] ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 11 and z_leader == "Stegerwald" and dnvp_ideology == "Radical": The <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> under Stegerwald is drawing a significant amount of frustrated <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> voters and members, steering them towards the <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span> instead of the special interest parties they would have otherwise supported, thanks to the party's recent reforms. It seems that the <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span> will be the party of the right, taking the place of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 12 : Austria's constitution has been amended to grant the President increased powers, including the authority to dismiss parliament, along with introducing direct presidential elections by the people. This has transformed Austria into a semi-presidential system of government, not too dissimilar to our own. The amendment was a result of a compromise with the <span style="color: #000000;">Christian Social Party</span>'s push for a more authoritarian and centralized government, as they needed the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Austrian Social Democrats</span>' approval to pass the amendment. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 12 and csvd_formed = 1 and stegerwald_path = 0: The Christian Social faction of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> have formed their own political party by merging with the CVD, to form the <span style="color: #8ED8E4;">Christian Social People's Service</span> (<span style="color: #8ED8E4;">**CSVD**</span>). The party mainly has support among Protestant workers, and refuses to cooperate with other bourgeois parties. They are surprisingly taking a hard stance towards the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>, decrying their "un-Christian excessive hatred of <span style="color: #005EB8;">Jews</span>". ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1929 and month = 12 and dnvp_historical_1929: The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> secessionists have joined forces with the <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">Christian-National Peasants' and Farmers' Party</span>(<span style="color: #7FCEB1;">**CNBLP**</span>) to establish the Christian-National Coalition, a new parliamentary faction in the Reichstag under the leadership of Treviranus. While this cooperation appears to signal a step toward unity among the anti-Hugenberg right, the <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">**CNBLP**</span> still claims that this alliance is merely a temporary measure driven by the parliamentary weakness of both groups. The primary barrier to further unification of the right-wing opposition remains the determination of the various parties to preserve their distinct ideological and vocational identities. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 1 and dnvp_historical_1929 and not (other_votes < 11 or peoples_party or weimar_coalition >= 50 or pro_republic < 40): The "Young Conservative" faction that split from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> a few months ago has officially established the "People's Conservative Association." This follows a disastrous meeting with other <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> dissidents, which ended in the failure to create even a loose federation of conservative forces. The association is not yet a formal party but aims to unify the <span style="color: #8ED8E4;">CSVD</span> and <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">CNBL</span> into a single bloc, hoping to field a joint list in the next election. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 1 and dnvp_historical_1929 and (peoples_party or weimar_coalition >= 50 or stegerwald_path or (z_leader == "Joos" and dvp_reform)): The "Young Conservative" faction that split from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> a few months ago has officially established the "<span style="color: #0087DC;">Conservative People's Party</span>" (<span style="color: #0087DC;">**KVP**</span>). One of their biggest backers is General Kurt von Schleicher, a close advisor of President Hindenburg and a militarist. They accepted the funds from Schleicher due to [? if stegerwald_path and z_leader == "Stegerwald": a drought in contributions from German industry, despite concerns over indepedence. ?][? if (z_leader == "Joos" and dvp_reform) or z_leader == "Kaiser": the conditional backing of German industry, who no longer have a home in the German party system, despite concerns over indepedence. ?][? if (weimar_coalition >= 50 or peoples_party) and not stegerwald_path and not (z_leader == "Joos" and dvp_reform): a desperation to combat our popularity, despite concerns over indepedence. ?] The funds were too substantial to ignore, silencing internal dissent among the other <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> splinter groups and uniting the conservative forces into a single entity. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if flavour_4_trigger == 1 and flavour_4_trigger_time == time: President Hindenburg is rumoured to be disenchanted with the current <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> government and may be working to find another government without our participation. If a crisis were to arise, it would certainly be used as a pretext to dismiss us from the government. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 1 and pro_republic < 65 and ddp_ideology != "Left" and z_ideology == "Right" and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> along with other bourgeois parties have increasingly been abandoning coalitions with us on the local level in favor of forming *Bürgerblocks* instead. We have lost control of prominent state governments. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 1 : Spanish dictator Miguel Primo de Rivera has resigned, as the Spanish people have grown tired with the dictatorship, especially after the onset of the economic depression. King Alfonso XIII has appointed a new dictator to govern in his place, but republican forces in the fragile kingdom are gaining significant support among the people. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 2 and z_ideology == "Right": Franz von Papen, a Catholic conservative known for obstructing Braun's appointment as Minister-President years ago, has been selected by Kaas and Brüning to fill a vacant Landtag seat. Positioned on the far right of his party, Papen is coming out of retirement despite being denied a seat by Joseph Hess and the left wing of the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> in the last election. To say the least, this is not a good sign for our longstanding cooperation with the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> over the course of the Republic. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 2 and dvp_leader = "Scholz" and in_grand_coalition and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> have convened a party congress to discuss important matters regarding cooperation with us and the future of our governmental coalition. During the congress, they have vocally supported the Grand coalition, and Scholz changed his stance, reversing his earlier opposition to cooperation with the bourgeois parties. We doubt the genuineness of their statements. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 2 and dvp_leader != "Scholz" and in_grand_coalition and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> have convened a party congress to discuss important matters regarding cooperation with us and the future of our governmental coalition. During the congress, they have vocally supported the Grand coalition, and have been especially been focused in promoting cooperation between the bourgeois parties. Perhaps the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> has finally come to its senses. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 2 and dvp_leader = "Scholz" and not in_grand_coalition and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> have convened a party congress to discuss important matters regarding the future of cooperation with us and the matter of bourgeois unity. During the congress, they ruled out any future coalitions with us. However, Scholz has reversed his earlier opposition to cooperating with the bourgeois parties as a result of pressure from Hans Luther and their industrialist backers. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 2 and dvp_leader != "Scholz" and not in_grand_coalition and not lvp_formed: The <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> have convened a party congress to discuss important matters regarding the future of cooperation with us and the matter of bourgeois unity. During the congress, they have especially been focused on promoting cooperation between the bourgeois parties and reaffirmed warm relations with us. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 3 and dvp_leader != "Luther" and lvp_leader != "Luther": Reichsbank president Hjalmar Schacht has resigned from his position. Former Chancellor and <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> member Hans Luther has been given the position. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 3 and not lvp_formed: More and more <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> leftists are being sidelined or pushed out of the party all in an effort to shed its pacifist and <span style="color: #c00000;">socialists</span> image, to appease their wealthy business backers and appeal increasingly right-wing German electorate. Former long-time leader of the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> left wing, Anton Erkelenz, was forced to retire late last year as his left-wing views became increasingly out of place. The leftists who remain in the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">[+ ddp_name +]</span>, now constituted as the 'Social Republican Circle', have largely conformed to the party's rightward shift. Despite this, they are still an obstacle for the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>'s business wing to overcome. ?]{!</p>!}

