{!<p class="other">!}[? if lvp_merger_2_timer == 1 and not lvp_formed: A <span style="color: #FFCC00;">united liberal party</span> is increasingly seeming likely, as negotiations between the moderates of both parties have produced surprisingly fruitful results. Despite this success, as always, the right wing of the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> and the left wing of the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> have remained a massive obstacle to liberal unity. Leaders of both parties have called an emergency party congress to settle this disagreement once and for all, but the declining vote shares of both parties are a major factor swaying the rank and file towards unification, and it's unlikely the opinion of the minority will come out on top. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 8: The last <span style="color: #002654;">French</span> and <span style="color: #FFD500;">Belgian</span> troops in the Rhineland have been evacuated in accordance with the Young Plan. While this is a positive development for the Republic, conservative elites within the Reichswehr and Hindenburg's inner circle are now free from external restraints to replace our system of government with an <span style="color: #808080;">authoritarian</span> and <span style="color: #7A3C00;">militarist</span> one.?]

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year >= 1931 and dnvp_split_2 and bourgeois_negotiations == 0 and not lvp_formed: Following Westarp's split from Hugenberg's <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>, [+ dvp_leader +] has taken a keen interest in fostering closer ties with him and his group of moderates. However, Westarp himself has little interest in merging with other parties, and is only willing to pursue closer bourgeois cooperation due to conditional industrial funding. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if bourgeois_negotiations_elections_1930_timer == 2 and bourgeois_negotiations_election_soon and dnvp_split_2 and (dvp_leader == "Scholz" or dvp_leader == "Dingeldey") and not lvp_formed: Following Westarp's split from Hugenberg's <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>, [+ dvp_leader +] has taken a keen interest in fostering closer ties with him and his group of moderates. The calling of new elections has given [? if dvp_leader == "Scholz": Scholz?][? if dvp_leader != "Scholz": the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>?] another opportunity to negotiate bourgeois unity. However, this time, the effort is far more ambitious—an appeal for the consolidation of all state-supporting forces, rather than just the formation of a parliamentary group. While Westarp himself has little interest in merging with other parties, he is willing to participate due to conditional industrial funding, which is contingent on achieving bourgeois unity. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if bourgeois_negotiations_elections_1930_timer == 2 and bourgeois_negotiations_election_soon and csvd_formed: The <span style="color: #8ED8E4;">**CSVD**</span>'s leadership has voted overwhelmingly in favor of entering the election with its own slate of candidates, explicitly rejecting any agreements with other parties for fear of compromising its identity. For the same reason, the <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">**CNBLP**</span> and <span style="color: #b8996f;">**WP**</span> have also dismissed Scholz's proposal for negotiations. Furthermore, the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> has criticized the proposal as a premature initiative that lacked the necessary consensus on such fundamental issues. ?]{!</p>!}

# if bourgeois group formed in first negotiations, write new text...

{!<p class="other">!}[? if bourgeois_negotiations_elections_1930_timer == 1 and bourgeois_negotiations_election_soon and dstp_formed: The formation of the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> and unsuccessful attempts to poach <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span> members have left a sour taste in their mouths. Despite this, negotiations between the parties [+ dvp_leader +] had invited continue, evoking cool responses from the other parties on [+ dvp_leader +]'s proposal for a united middle party. This has caused [+ dvp_leader +] to scale down his ambitions, and instead propose an electoral truce and a joint election appeal in favor of[? if chancellor == "Brüning":&nbsp;Brüning and?] President Hindenburg. Although accepted by all parties at first, opposition from the old guard in the <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">**CNBLP**</span> and <span style="color: #b8996f;">**WP**</span> has obstructed this proposal, but eventually, due to conditional industrial funding, the 'Hindenburg Program' is supported by only the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>, <span style="color: #b8996f;">**WP**</span>, and <span style="color: #0087DC;">**KVP**</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 8: The film adaptation of the controversial anti-war novel *All Quiet on the Western Front* has released in America, but has yet to arrive on our shores. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="dnvp">!}[? if flavour_3_trigger == 1 and flavour_3_trigger_time == time : Negotiations to unite the various splinter groups from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has failed to achieve any results, the <span style="color: #0087DC;">**KVP**</span> is expected to perform poorly due to its lack of a political base of its own, unlike the[? if stegerwald_path = 0:&nbsp;<span style="color: #8ED8E4;">Christian Socialists</span> and?] <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">agrarians</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 10: <span style="color: #009739;">Br</span><span style="color: #FEDD00;">az</span><span style="color: #009739;">il</span> has undergone a revolution, replacing the First Republic with the Second Republic and bringing Getúlio Vargas into power following a disputed presidential election result earlier in the year. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1930 and month = 11 : The <span style="color: #C8102E;">Austrian Social Democrats</span> have won the recent legislative election, securing a majority of seats in their *Nationalrat*. However a right-wing coalition of the <span style="color: #000000;">Christian Social Party</span> and minor bourgeois parties once again has excluded them from government. The Austrian branch of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> have received 3% of the vote, and the political wing of the <span style="color: #ABDDA4;">Heimwehr</span> (comparable to our *Freikorps*) garnered 6%. This is particularly concerning, as the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Austrian Social Democrats</span> lost votes despite the economic depression occurring while they were in opposition, suggesting the electorate is looking for answers on the right. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1931 and month = 4 : The Second Spanish Republic has been established, replacing the monarchy of Alfonso XIII. This follows municipal elections in wich republican candidates scored significant victories, winning in all 41 provincial capitals. This has forced the king into exile and a new, young republic has been created. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if banking_crisis_timer == 1 : The major Austrian Bank Creditanstalt has declared bankruptcy, following <span style="color: #002654;">French</span> political and economic pressures aimed at undermining the plans for the Austro-German customs union. In that respect, they have certainly succeeded. We can only hope that this crisis does not spill over into Germany or, worse, spread across Europe. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1931 and month = 6 : The first elections of the Second Spanish Republic has been held, with it a great victory for the <span style="color: #EF1C27;">Spanish Socialists</span> and the <span style="color: #E25822;">Republican Left</span>. Together, they've formed a government with Manuel Azaña as Prime Minister. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1931 and month = 9: The Japanese have invaded Manchuria following the Mukden incident. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="both">!}[? if year = 1931 and month = 10: The recent United Kingdom general elections have resulted in the greatest landslide in the country's history, with <span style="color: #f0456a;">Labour</span> receiving only a meager 52 seats, losing 235 of them from the previous election. Despite this, the incumbent <span style="color: #008000;">National Labour</span> Prime Minister Ramsay MacDonald has remained in office, ruling with the <span style="color: #0087DC;">Tories</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1931 and month = 12 : The new Second Spanish Republic has adopted its new democratic constitution, establishing a secular, progressive, and republican government. Times are looking bright for Spain. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1932 and month = 5 : <span style="color: #002654;">France</span> held its legislative elections this month, resulting in a majority for the <span style="color: #FFC0C0;">Left Cartel</span>, and a decline in the vote share for the <span style="color: #88001A;">French Communists</span>. However, the <span style="color: #F0001C;">**SFIO**</span> has refused to participate in government, prompting the <span style="color: #E0B0FF;">Radical Socialists</span> to form a coalition with the center-right instead. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1932 and month = 5 : The Austrian government has resigned due to the significant gains of the Austrian <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> in recent local elections, leading to Engelbert Dollfuß being appointed chancellor by the President. Dollfuß now rules in a coalition with the <span style="color: #ABDDA4;">Heimwehr</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1932 and month = 8 : Austria has obtained a League of Nations loan that is tied to a 20-year ban on Anschluss, but opposition from the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Social Democrats</span> and <span style="color: #0E428E;">Greater German Party</span> has stalled the law, before it finally is passed by a single vote. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1932 and month = 9 : General elections were held in Sweden, resulting in a great victory for Per Albin Hansson and his <span style="color: #D70926;">Social Democrats</span>, who now govern in a minority government. The <span style="color: #D70926;">Swedish Social Democrats</span> have embraced the concept of a 'people's home', a form of reformist socialism aimed at reducing class divides while working in the capitalist framework. Perhaps we should consider following their 'nordic' model? ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1932 and month = 10 : Chancellor of Austria Engelbert Dollfuß has used the "War Economy Enabling Act", a law passed during the days of the Austro-Hungarian Empire, which allowed him to restructure the Creditanstalt without parliamentary approval. While the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Austrian Social Democrats</span> have protested, Dollfuß' actions are technically legal. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1932 and month = 11 : <span style="color: #00AEF3;">Democrat</span> Franklin D. Roosevelt has defeated incumbent <span style="color: #E81B23;">Republican</span> President Herbert Hoover in a landslide in the <span style="color: #B31942;">United</span> <span style="color: #0A3161;">States</span> presidential election. This is attributed by the Great Depression and Roosevelt's campaigning for a "New Deal", proposing expansive public works and government reform. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1933 and month = 3 and not ((spd_in_government and foreign_minister_party = "SPD") or (austria_relation >= 1)): Dollfuß has abused his powers given in the "War Economy Enabling Act" to crack down on the workers in a railroad strike, which has resulted in all three presidents of parliament resigning amid a crucial vote. This crisis presented a perfect opportunity for Dollfuß to abolish the parliamentary system and restrict democratic rights, such as the freedom of the press and public protests. Another democracy has fell to authoritarianism. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1933 and month = 5 : Dollfuß's <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Austrofascist</span> dictatorship has banned the <span style="color: #700000;">Austrian Communists</span> and the paramilitary of the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Austrian Social Democrats</span>, the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Republican Protection League</span>. He has also established the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Fatherland Front</span>, a party promoting a far-right <span style="color: #7A3C00;">fascist</span> and corporate ideology. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1933 and month = 11 : The <span style="color: #EF1C27;">Spanish Socialists</span> and the <span style="color: #E25822;">Republican Left</span> have suffered an overwhelming defeat at the hands of the right wing <span style="color: #303180;">**CEDA**</span> and increasingly right-wing <span style="color: #A871A8;">Radicals</span>. ?]{!</p>!}

{!<p class="other">!}[? if year = 1934 and month = 2 and not austrian_parliament_seen: The Austrian Civil War has begun and ended in a matter of three days, fought between the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Republican Protection League</span> and Austria's <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Austrofascist</span> regime, resulting in a defeat for the <span style="color: #C8102E;">socialists</span> across the border. The uprising was sparked by efforts to suppress the remnants of the <span style="color: #C8102E;">Austrian Social Democrats</span> and their paramilitary wing. However, the poorly coordinated and weakened movement was swiftly crushed by the army. Perhaps things would have gone more differently if they have taken up arms earlier. ?]{!</p>!}

{!</div>!}

